üìò WEEK 3 ‚Äì DAY 5 JavaScript | DOM & BOM

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
üéØ Goal of Day 5

‚úî Understand **DOM (Document Object Model)**
‚úî Understand **BOM (Browser Object Model)**
‚úî Learn how JavaScript interacts with **HTML & Browser**
‚úî Build dynamic and interactive web pages

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üå≥ What is DOM?

**DOM (Document Object Model)** represents the **HTML document as a tree structure**.

* Every HTML element becomes a **node**
* JavaScript uses DOM to:

  * Access HTML
  * Modify HTML
  * Change styles
  * Handle events

üìå DOM connects **HTML + JavaScript**

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üß† DOM Tree Example

```
document
 ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ html
     ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ head
     ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ body
         ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ h1
         ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ p
```

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üîç Accessing HTML Elements (DOM Methods)

By ID

```js
document.getElementById("title");
```

---

By Class Name

```js
document.getElementsByClassName("box");
```

---

By Tag Name

```js
document.getElementsByTagName("p");
```

---

querySelector (Most Used ‚≠ê)

```js
document.querySelector(".box");
document.querySelector("#title");
```

---

querySelectorAll

```js
document.querySelectorAll("p");
```

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

‚úèÔ∏è Changing HTML Content

innerHTML

```js
document.getElementById("title").innerHTML = "Hello DOM";
```

---

textContent

```js
element.textContent = "Text only";
```

üìå `textContent` is safer than `innerHTML`

---
üé® Changing CSS with DOM

```js
element.style.color = "red";
element.style.backgroundColor = "yellow";
```

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

‚ûï Creating & Removing Elements

Create Element

```js
let div = document.createElement("div");
div.textContent = "New Element";
document.body.appendChild(div);
```

---

Remove Element

```js
element.remove();
```

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üß© DOM Attributes

Get Attribute

```js
element.getAttribute("id");
```

---

Set Attribute

```js
element.setAttribute("class", "active");
```

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üñ±Ô∏è DOM Events

Events happen when users interact.

Add Event Listener (Best Practice ‚≠ê)

```js
button.addEventListener("click", function () {
  alert("Button clicked");
});
```

Common Events:

* `click`
* `mouseover`
* `keydown`
* `submit`
* `change`

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üåê What is BOM?

**BOM (Browser Object Model)** allows JavaScript to interact with the **browser window**.

üìå BOM is NOT related to HTML
üìå BOM controls browser features

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üß† Important BOM Objects

window

```js
window.alert("Hello");
```

---

screen

```js
screen.width;
screen.height;
```

---

location

```js
location.href;
location.reload();
```

---

history

```js
history.back();
history.forward();
```

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

navigator

```js
navigator.userAgent;
navigator.language;
```

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üÜö DOM vs BOM

| DOM                  | BOM                |
| -------------------- | ------------------ |
| Works with HTML      | Works with browser |
| Document-based       | Window-based       |
| Changes page content | Controls browser   |

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üîî Timers in BOM

setTimeout

```js
setTimeout(() => {
  console.log("Executed after 2 seconds");
}, 2000);
```

---

setInterval

```js
setInterval(() => {
  console.log("Repeating");
}, 1000);
```

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

‚ùå Common Beginner Mistakes

* Using `innerHTML` unnecessarily
* Forgetting event listeners
* Manipulating DOM before page load
* Confusing DOM with BOM

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üí° Best Practices

* Use `querySelector`
* Use `addEventListener`
* Avoid inline JS
* Minimize DOM manipulation
* Use `textContent` when possible

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

‚úÖ DAY-5 Summary (Week-3)

* DOM structure & access
* Modify HTML & CSS
* DOM events
* BOM objects
* DOM vs BOM differences
* Real-world usage
